dgingIT.DevKit.Presentation.Web","summary":"Creates a route group and applies the shared endpoint group configuration from the supplied options.","remarks":"The method validates app and options before mapping. It creates the group with BridgingIT.DevKit.Presentation.Web.EndpointsOptionsBase.GroupPath, optionally normalizes the path, applies tags, OpenAPI group metadata, description visibility, authorization or anonymous metadata, CORS metadata, rate limiting metadata, route name prefix metadata, and custom metadata. Authorization role entries and authentication schemes that are blank are ignored. Anonymous access takes precedence over authorization metadata. Example: var group = MapGroup(app, options); group.MapGet(\u0022items\u0022, GetItems) .WithName(BuildRouteName(options, \u0022GetItems\u0022));","syntax":{"content":"public RouteGroupBuilder MapGroup(IEndpointRouteBuilder app, EndpointsOptionsBase options)","parameters":[{"id":"app","type":"Microsoft.AspNetCore.Routing.IEndpointRouteBuilder","description":"The endpoint route builder that owns the new group."},{"id":"options","type":"BridgingIT.DevKit.Presentation.Web.EndpointsOptionsBase","description":"The endpoint group options to apply."}],"returns":{"type":"Microsoft.AspNetCore.Routing.RouteGroupBuilder","description":"A configured route group builder that callers can use to map individual endpoints."}},"parameters":[{"id":"app","type":"Microsoft.AspNetCore.Routing.IEndpointRouteBuilder","description":"The endpoint route builder that owns the new group."},{"id":"options","type":"BridgingIT.DevKit.Presentation.Web.EndpointsOptionsBase","description":"The endpoint group options to apply."}],"returns":{"type":"Microsoft.AspNetCore.Routing.RouteGroupBuilder","description":"A configured route group builder that callers can use to map individual endpoints."},"parent":"BridgingIT.DevKit.Presentation.Web.EndpointsBase","children":[],"extensionMethods":[],"examples":[],"url":"https://bridgingit-gmbh.github.io/bITdev